reviews.review_text:
Play the Band I was in the hallway at the Coliseum before the show.  Someone passed out flyers, which read, "When the band comes onstage, let's show them our appreciation by chanting, 'You know our love will not fade away.'  Maybe the music will play the band, and they will open with Playin'"  Still considering myself a newbie (8 yrs, but only about 20 shows), I thought this was pretty arrogant.  I joined in anyway (note "Playing Chant"), and we pulled it off.  The boys looked around, in amazement then did PITB!!!  I had forgotten about this for some time, until I streamed the show recently.  Some really good days back then.  All the years combine...they really DID melt into a dream!

Recommend listeners check out the Henry Kaiser recordings on Archive.org.

Archive.org is amazing!  Thank you guys.

Don't be fooled! This is if not the worst, definite one of the worst New Year's shows ever! I'm sorry if you think you it was good, but please compare others such as 81-82 (best ever) for example, or even the closing of Winterland is much better than this. They get progressively worse after '82.
